imdb.title: Sairento mebiusu
imdb.plot: A team of policewomen with supernatural powers try to protect the Earth from an alien invasion known as the Lucifer Hawks.

episodes.title: Kakusei (Awake)
episodes.plot: A young woman, Katsumi Liqueur gets invited by police chief Rally Cheyenne to the area of Tokyo on a promise of giving her information about her late mother. But what she doesn't know is that she gets enlisted to the AMP to fight the Lucifer Hawk.

episodes.title: Ketsudan (Decide)
episodes.plot: A Lucifer Hawk breaks through the AMP gate to try to give Katsumi information on her father. Also, The Lucifer Hawks have broken through into the city.

episodes.title: Tôkyô no Soko (Tokyo Underground)
episodes.plot: Robert gives Katsumi some police training to try to defeat the Lucifer Hawk.

episodes.title: Bureiku-in (Brake In)
episodes.plot: Katsumi tries to defeat a Category 2 Lucifer Hawk by herself which gets her in trouble with Rally Cheyenne.

episodes.title: Pâti no Yoru (Let's Have a Party)
episodes.plot: Yuki Saiko decides to throw a fun party for everyone.

episodes.title: Owarinaki Takakai: Megadyne
episodes.plot: Kiddy Phenyl recalls her memories of almost being killed by a Megadyne cyborg named Wire.

episodes.title: Ushiro no Shômen: Kagome Kagome
episodes.plot: Nami Yamigumo goes back to her Japanese Shinto temple to meet with her grandfather.

episodes.title: Keishô: Yes, My Master!
episodes.plot: Katsumi tries to defeat a Category 1 Lucifer Hawk by herself without the other team members but it causes her to lose her dagger.

episodes.title: Katsute Aishita Michikado: Tokyo Antique
episodes.plot: Katsumi's apartment has been damaged by the battles with the Lucifer Hawks, so she decides to stay with the other AMP members.

episodes.title: XRP-77
episodes.plot: Yuki hears the bad news that her two friends from her childhood were killed and this awakens her past memories.

episodes.title: Kikaijikake no Arisu: Alice in Logic-space
episodes.plot: The computer networks have been hacked in Tokyo by somebody that has been using a image of a Cheshire cat and the city is now at a stand still, The AMP team try to find the hacker.

episodes.title: Norowareta Kizuna: Sister
episodes.plot: Ganossa Maximilian and Rosa Cheyenne make a plan to take over the human world, and Rosa comes to Rally to kill her.

episodes.title: Category-IV
episodes.plot: It has been six months since Katsumi has left the AMP team and is now living with Roy De Vice. The board team has now acknowledged the Lucifer Hawks's extra terrestrials, but Roy does not know that Nemisis blood is coursing though Katsumi's veins.

episodes.title: Mobius Klein (Jokyoku)
episodes.plot: Rally tells Katsumi the story of the Silent Crisis and what Katsumi's father wanted to achieve with Project Gaia.

episodes.title: Lum Chang (Kaorun no Shojo)
episodes.plot: The AMP gets a new member, a Chinese girl named Lum Cheng.

episodes.title: Labyrinth (Koku no Meikyu)
episodes.plot: Yuki goes to an antique shop because she wants to purchase a coffee grinder, but she finds out that the owner is a Lucifer Hawk. During their fight, Yuki and the Lucifer Hawk go thirty years to the past of pre-apocalyptic Tokyo. When she awakens she finds been taken care of by a young man named Toru Washio. She teaches him how to make coffee.

episodes.title: Destiny (Musubiau Yube)
episodes.plot: Kiddy Phenyl has been charge with a murder of that is based on circumstantial evidence and gets arrested while on the chase of a magadyne tat happens to be the real culprit. Her boyfriend Ralph knows that she is innocent.

episodes.title: Domull
episodes.plot: The Mobile Police Division does an investigation that only has a single survivor, a young girl. Also Ralph and Roy find that a drug is being distributed by their superiors called Domull which can turn humans into monsters.

episodes.title: Back of a Coin
episodes.plot: Lum Cheng decides to take Katsumi on a drive to seaside to brighten her day. But when they get there, they find the rest of the AMP team there already.

episodes.title: Love
episodes.plot: The AMP rescues Roy from the evil Lucifer hawk and Rosa has attacked Rally back at the AMP headquarters. Ganossa kidnaps Katsumi and holds her hostage in a test that will make Roy show how much he truly loves her.

episodes.title: Tsuki no Umareta Yoru: Dark Side of the Moon
episodes.plot: Kiddy has organized a reunion party at a cafe and Katsumi decides to go to it.

episodes.title: Anten: Crying
episodes.plot: Rally wants Mana to increase the security protection around the Avalance files because they contain data on Project Gaia.

episodes.title: Saisen Seshimono: Life Again
episodes.plot: Katsumi has revealed herself to be a traitor and the AMP might be disbanded and Yuki can't seem to control her powers.

episodes.title: Jigoku e no Michi: Hell Road
episodes.plot: Ganossa has invited Rally to meet him alone at the Tokyo Stadium to which she agrees even though she thinks it's a trap. She gets caught in a spell by Nami who is under the control of Ganossa.

episodes.title: Shito: Count Down
episodes.plot: Katsumi is now possessed by the Medium and wants to take control of the AMP and she attacks her former team members.

episodes.title: Kibo: Tomorrow
episodes.plot: It has been a week since the AMP building was destroyed and the Tokyo Administration has publicly announced the existence of the Lucifer Hawk. The AMP members are in the hospital. The Tokyo Administration is requiring the evacuation of the entire Tokyo population in case theirs future Lucifer Hawk attacks.
